# Project Structure

## Laravel Standard Structure

### Application Code (`app/`)
- `Http/Controllers/` - Single-action controllers using `__invoke()` method
- `Models/` - Eloquent models
- `Providers/` - Service providers
- `View/Components/` - Blade components
- `Filament/` - Admin panel resources (auto-discovered)

### Frontend (`resources/`)
- `views/` - Blade templates
- `components/` - Reusable Blade components
- `css/app.css` - Main stylesheet (Tailwind)
- `js/app.js` - Main JavaScript entry point

### Configuration (`config/`)
Standard Laravel configuration files for database, cache, mail, etc.

### Database (`database/`)
- `migrations/` - Database schema changes
- `seeders/` - Database seeders
- `factories/` - Model factories for testing

### Public Assets (`public/`)
- `images/` - Static images and media
- `build/` - Compiled assets (generated by Vite)
- Generated Filament assets in `css/filament/` and `js/filament/`

## Conventions

### Controllers
- Use single-action controllers with `__invoke()` method
- Follow naming: `{Feature}Controller` (e.g., `HomeController`, `DonateController`)
- Keep controllers thin, delegate business logic to services/models

### Views
- Use kebab-case for view names (`about-us.blade.php`, `contact-us.blade.php`)
- Leverage `<x-app-layout>` component for consistent layout
- Store reusable components in `resources/components/`

### Routes
- Web routes in `routes/web.php`
- API routes in `routes/api.php`
- Admin routes handled by Filament automatically

### Filament Admin
- Resources auto-discovered in `app/Filament/Resources/`
- Pages auto-discovered in `app/Filament/Pages/`
- Widgets auto-discovered in `app/Filament/Widgets/`
- Admin panel accessible at `/admin` route

### Assets
- Use Vite for asset compilation
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Store images in `public/images/`
- Compiled assets go to `public/build/`